property.description:
RAY COOKE AUCTIONEERS proudly present this exceptional four-bedroom end of terrace extended home in the highly sought after “Crosforge” development, perfectly located in the heart of Saggart Village, Co Dublin. The village of Saggart has plenty to recommend for home buyers, especially those looking to move out of the city. It retains a rural feel despite being close to the city, with some beautiful scenery nearby and an abundance of local amenities including schools, shops and eateries. Transport wise, the location is next to none as the area is well serviced by excellent transport links from numerous bus routes to the Red Line Luas just a 5-minute walk away. Beautifully extended, sophisticated and tastefully decorated living accommodation of c. 178 sqm can be found in this bright and spacious home which in brief comprises of; entrance porch, hallway, living room, w.c, utility room and large open plan kitchen/diner to the rear which opens out onto a low maintenance rear garden which benefits from a highly sought after south west orientation. On the 1st floor you will find the family bathroom and three double bedrooms with master benefitting from ensuite bath, all rooms are fully fitted with built in wardrobes and top-quality flooring. On the 2nd floor you have another master bedroom with ensuite bathroom. You benefit from a high degree of privacy here. To the rear you have a paved seating area along with a storage shed and side access. To the front of the property which provides off street parking for a selection of vehicles. No.16 is presented in truly show home condition from top to bottom after being meticulously maintained and upgraded by its current owners. It is situated in one of Saggarts most sought after developments and comes to the market with no onward chain. Viewing is highly advised to fully appreciate the benefits that this fantastic home has to offer.

Additional Features;
– B1 rated BER
– C 178 sqm
– Energy efficient construction
– 4 bed 4 bath
– End of terrace home
– Heavily extended
– Large open plan kitchen/dining
– Fully fitted kitchen
– Integrated appliances
– Stunning breakfast island
– Beautiful feature wall
– Four double bedrooms
– X2 large master bedrooms with ensuite
– Built in wardrobes
– Large utility room
– Fitted cabinets
– Guest WC
– Top quality fixtures & fittings
– Top quality flooring
– Top quality blinds throughout
– No forward chain
– Low maintenance rear garden
– Sunny south west orientation
– Shed to rear for storage
– Designated parking
– Immaculately presented throughout
– Double glazed PVC windows and doors
– Family oriented development
– Close to all local amenities
– 10-minute walk to Saggart luas stop
– Viewing is highly advised

Directions coming off the N7 at the Rathcoole/Saggart junction, take the first exit onto Mill road towards Saggart. Take the first exit at the next roundabout you reach and proceed towards village. At the cross roads, take a right turn onto Castle Road and then take your second right onto Crosforge Close. Take your first right onto Crosforge and follow the road around to the left where number 16 will be on your left-hand side
